ROOT CAUSE ANALYSIS (RCA) REPORT — CENTRIFUGAL PUMP P-401
Incident Ref: IR-2024-118 | Report ID: RCA-001 | Asset: Centrifugal Pump P-401
Created By: Reliability Engineer (Asrawool28) | Incident Date: 2026-07-18

1. INCIDENT SYMPTOMS
- Excessive vibration > 4.2 mm/s (Peak recorded: 5.8 mm/s).
- Bearing housing temperature rise 12°C above baseline (reaching 78°C).
- Abnormal high-frequency screeching noise reported by Plant Operations.

2. ROOT CAUSES IDENTIFIED
- Cause 1: Bearing starvation due to grease degradation at elevated summer ambient operating temperatures (42°C).
- Cause 2: Relubrication interval set too long (2000 operating hours).
- Cause 3: High-vibration operating regime caused by minor pipe strain on suction header.

3. CORRECTIVE ACTIONS & WORK ORDER CONVERSION
- Action 1: Reduce lube interval from 2000h to 1400h (Updated in Technical Manual TM-P401-001).
- Action 2: Converted to Work Order WO-101 ("P-401 Bearing & Lubrication Service") for immediate execution.
- Action 3: Update SOP §6.3 for high-temperature operating protocols.
- Cross-Record Insight Note: Statutory inspection INSP-001 on P-401 was 10 days overdue prior to this incident.